Erdogan at Office for First Time Since Surgery Two Weeks Ago

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-12-10T11:26:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-10/erdogan-at-office-for-first-time-since-surgery-two-weeks-ago-1-.html
Turkish Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip Erdogan  worked at his office in Istanbul’s Dolmabahce Palace
following abdominal surgery two weeks ago.  Erdogan left his home in the Uskudar district of the city
for the first time since starting to recuperate from the
operation on Nov. 26, state-run Anatolia news agency said. He
returned home after 1.5 hours, it said.  Anatolia didn’t provide any details about his program for
the coming days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Bentley at 
 mbentley3@bloomberg.net  